<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="28Aug1918"><font color="red">28 August 1918</font>, <cite>Yale</cite> (JJ to Ezra Pound): Thanks for your card and good opinion of the Hades episode. I sent you some days ago express the Eolus episode &hellip; I have not seen any issue of the <cite>Little Review</cite> since the June issue &hellip; I shall send you as quickly as I can the Lestrygonians and after that the Hamlet chapter (Scylla and Charybdis). I received  your M.O. (&pound;10) and thank you very much. If you need a collective receipt for the &pound;30 I shall send it on demand &hellip; I am house-hunting &hellip; I was quite comfortable in these rooms till the adjoining hospital bought the house &hellip; Lewis &hellip; sent me a copy of <cite>Tarr</cite>.</div>
